#PROGRAMMING EXERCISE 15 : THE MONTH OF FEB HAS 28 DAYS. LEAP YEAR IS 29 DAYS. WRITE A PROGRAM THAT ASK THE USER
#TO ENTER A YEAR. THEN DISPLAY THE NUMBER OF DAYS IN FEB THAT YEAR. USE THE FOLLOWING:
#DETERMINE IF THE YEAR IS DIVISIBLE BY 100. IF IT IS, THEN IT IS A LEAP YEAR IF AND ONLY IF IT IS ALSO DIVISIBLE BY 400.
#IF THE YEAR IS NOT DIVISIBLE BY 100,THEN IT IS A LEAP YEAR IF AND ONLY IF IT IS DIVISBLE BY 4. FOR EXAMPLE, 2008 IS A LEAP 
#YEAR BUT 2009 IS NOT.

#ASK USER FOR INPUT:
year= int(input("Enter a year: "))

#CALCULATE LEAP YEAR
if year % 100 == 0:
      if year % 400 ==0:
            print (f"In {year} February has 29 days!")
      else:
            print(f"In {year} February has 28 days!")
elif year % 4 == 0:
      print (f"In {year} February has 29 days!")
else:
      print(f"In {year} February has 28 days!")



